(54, 64, 48, 0, 'davidadamshirley@gmail.com', 'We now have 115 people registered for eye testing and possible cataract operations in May. We expect to have over 300 registered by the end of April. All registered patients will have their eyes tested by the Perdamai team, in collaboration with the medical team at the health clinic. Doctors from puskesmas (village clinics)  have been recommending  patients to participate in the eye testing program. Eye Specialists will then prioritise operations based on a number of factors, for example some patients may have too high a blood pressure to be operated on. These patients will be given medication to reduce their blood pressure and offered alternative options to remove their cataract. This could include returning when the joint Perdamai/ Besi Pae community events.\r\n It is expected over 100 cataract operations will be performed in May.\r\n\r\nWe thank you again for your generous support.', '2016-04-12 10:39:01'),
