(15, 61, '2016-03-04', 'Rumah Baca Lintang', '<p style="text-align:justify">There are several stages to realize the movement of the green and child-friendly village. Both before and after the expiration of fundraising through Gotongroyong.fund, stages as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">1. Meeting Preparation: In a preparatory of this meeting, we describe for recent developments on the results of fundraising through GRF to all children of Rumah Baca Lintang. Then continuing to do a mapping for plants, pots and other materials needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Mapping of plants and other things needed, children of Rumah Baca Lintang count the number of houses, in order to calculate the cost of which is reserved for the purchase of plants, flowers, fruit trees, pots, bamboo, etc. To get a real picture of the number of homes, we coordinate with the secretary of PKK to obtain the data population based on the number of houses and households (families).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">2. Socializing with citizens: For the perception of the intent and purpose of the movement of the green and child-friendly village, then we make a socialization meeting with residents facilitated by Neighborhood Association (RT) and the Forum of citizens concerned about the environment. The meeting was placed on the streets village, which was attended by about 60 people, including children of Rumah Baca Lintang. We convey to the leaders community that in the meetings and activities there should be more involvement of children of Rumah Baca Lintang so that there is a learning process obtained by children of Rumah Baca Lintang expression. In this meeting, we explained the purpose of the green and child-friendly village and existing problems related lack of green spaces, scattered garbage and the importance to provide a protection to children. From the results of this meeting, citizens are ready and fully support for this movement, only the initial stages focused on the greening program and the bank bins advance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">3. On 24th of January, we hunted for plants and book various types of plants . On Sunday morning, 25th of January, the plants come . Types of plants that have been bought are composed of : Pine, red bud, tread pepper, plant longan, sapodilla fruit plants, plant lime, lemon and pacitan, small red chilli, eggplant, betel, mint, lipstick, croton, rhombus, Asoka, kemuning, kenanga, purslane, Parigata Lemon, cypress fan, capsicum Japan, lychees and some hanging plant species and plant seeds. Every types of plants has the amount of variety are 10-50 pcs/plant. There are pot sizes, large, medium and small purchasing, including compost purchasing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">4. On morning, 25<sup>th</sup> January at around 06.00am, reforestation activities commenced, beginning of distributing plants to citizens. Before the implementation of plant allocation, we are coordinating with Neighborhood Association (RT) and Chairman of the citizen forum to determine the number of plants will be received by each residents. From the results of coordination, we agreed that the plant is divided based on the house not the number of heads of families in the house.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<p>Rumah Baca Lintang Residents are so hilarious and surrounding to select and see the plant will be shared. Overlays streets village around Rumba Lintang filled with plants and citizens. Children of Rumba Lintang as green village movers were busy for choosing the type of plants that would be distributed to residents. For those residents who didn&rsquo;t come to take, the children of Rumba Lintang along with Neighborhood Association (RT) come to each resident&rsquo;s homes while bringing the plant, which is placed on a small cart. Each house gets 3-5 plants. Whether it&#39;s hanging plants or types of other plants.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<div>Immediately, almost all houses were busy of taking care the plants. There is also buy a new pot immediately, and then put the plants into pots. We don&rsquo;t provide too many pots, so that residents awoke to set aside a home budget conscious to buy pots and plants. In addition, due to our budget limited.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>The bustles of people to make the atmosphere village are so hilarious because all are excited to get plants. For citizens who have more money, they and other residents went to the flower market to buy plants that have not owned to make their homes are more green and lush. On that day, the activities were finish until 9 pm.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>5. On 31st January 2016, the activities continued with the painting of the right and left side edges of the village streets in paving with yellow and green. Painting has been done by children of Rumba Lintang and some residents, especially by mothers. Residents were still drawn. Mothers with pleasure have been providing Ice kopyor and snacks and other residents are still struggling to care of the plants as well as mutual sharing information and tips of plants treatment.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>As for the fathers, they are busy for making foundation and build a canopy of bamboo. Measuring of Canopy is 6 x 6 meters enabled for vines, for example, passion fruit and grapes. In order for the village streets more beautiful, green and shady because of many plants.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ngelom Along Gang 5, Taman - Sidoarjo looks green, clean and fresh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. What we have not done yet and will be implemented soon is to continue the painting located in a small alley. Painting will be done on Sunday, February 7, 2016. Replacing the canopy in the alley gate are, will be handled solely by Neighborhood Association (RT) and local community leaders because they want canopy material using the ferrous material, whereas the material that we have is Bamboo. Material has been changed because no such ground in the streets or in the dean houses that could be scooped.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>The Garbage Bank will have a re-discussion with the local community leaders, including the mothers. While there is an obstacle that no such temporary shelter for dry waste. We have proposes to garbage collection that has been aggregated by citizens, residents can bring to the Bank on every sunday. Weighing bins and administrative processes of Garbage Bank are doing on the location that has been determined. After the great collectors who are already willing to buy the junk comes to the garbage hauling. Providing that the activities of garbage banks only working on Sunday. Our proposal will be discussed and decided by the community leaders and local PKK.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Child-friendly village, there are still further discussions with residents and community leaders so that their output agreement or written rules on the protection of children released by the citizens forum and villages. While waiting for the formal process, we will put up flyers and posters in village streets with slogans for campaigns for the rights and protection of children.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>7. Financial reporting : A. Purchase of the first stage of the plants, pots, bamboo, gutter plastic, eating, fare transportation, banners, etc are Rp 8.477 million. B. Purchase of the second stage of the plants and seeds are Rp 1.022 million. C. Purchase of the third stage for paint, brushes, iron paint, wire, paranet, bamboo, pots, small and big nails, eating etc are Rp 1.497 million. D. Before the movement of green and child-friendly village, we are involved in the declaration day national fairy tales, as well as payments shirts for rewards to backers. The cost we spent are around Rp 1.369 million. The total funds that we ever used are Rp 12.365 million. The fund that has been received from GotongRoyong.fund are USD 14.05 million. Remaining funds are Rp 1.685 million.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>8. The rest of the remaining funds will be using to purchase the paint and installation Wi-Fi at Rumah Baca Lintang as a means access for technology and information to children and citizens.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>There are still some needs that we can&rsquo;t cover yet in this activity, for example, manufacture of play facilities, tent to read for children, bookshelves repair and the addition of a few plants.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Thus the development of the activity or movement green and child-friendly village by Rumah Baca Lintang that we can say. On any form of support for both the funding and morale to us, I personally and on behalf of the Rumah Baca Lintang say thank you so much.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>We wish all the good that has been given, will be given in exchange for love and fortune abundant of God Almighty. Amen.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Best Regards,</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong><u>M Theo Z</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Founder of Rumah Baca Lintang</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl22.jpeg" style="height:133px; width:227px" />&nbsp; <img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl23.jpeg" style="height:133px; width:228px" />&nbsp; <img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl9.jpeg" style="height:133px; width:227px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl1.jpeg" style="height:133px; width:227px" />&nbsp; <img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl2.jpeg" style="height:133px; width:227px" />&nbsp; <img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl10.jpeg" style="height:133px; width:227px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl5.jpeg" style="height:133px; width:227px" />&nbsp; <img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl4(1).jpeg" style="height:133px; width:227px" />&nbsp; <img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl11.jpeg" style="height:133px; width:227px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl3.jpeg" style="height:133px; width:227px" />&nbsp; <img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl6.jpeg" style="height:133px; width:227px" />&nbsp; <img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl15.jpeg" style="height:133px; width:227px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl7.jpeg" style="height:133px; width:227px" />&nbsp; <img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl8.jpeg" style="height:133px; width:227px" />&nbsp; <img alt="" src="http://www.gotongroyong.fund/uploads/project/rbl13.jpeg" style="height:133px; width:227px" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(16, 64, '2016-03-29', 'Jadwal Operasi Katarak ', '<p>Untuk Semua,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kami telah dikonfirmasikan oleh Perdami bahwa operasi katarak berikutnya akan dilaksanakan selama seminggu pada tanggal 1 - 5 Mei 2016. Kami memiliki tim yang terdiri dari 14 dokter dan perawat yang akan pergi ke Timor untuk melaksanakan operasi. Kami telah membeli peralatan untuk meminimalkan biaya logistik masa depan kami. Tiket dan akomodasi juga telah dipesan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tim Besi Pae sedang menginformasikan kepada masyarakat di TTS untuk pelayanan yang ditujukan. Kami berharap untuk memiliki lebih dari 300 orang yang menghadiri screening klinik mata dan melakukan lebih dari 100 operasi katarak.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kami berterima kasih atas dukungan keuangan Anda dan kami akan memberikan update reguler selama 5 minggu ke depan. Sumbangan tambahan dipersilahkan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Salam Hormat,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nico Ndun<br />\r\nBesi Pae</p>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(17, 64, '2016-04-12', 'Progress Operasi Katarak Mei 2016', '<p style="text-align:justify">Kami sekarang telah memiliki 115 orang yang terdaftar untuk pengujian mata dan operasi katarak pada bulan Mei. Kami berharap untuk memiliki lebih dari 300 yang terdaftar pada akhir April. Semua pasien yang terdaftar akan melaksanakan tes pengujian mata oleh tim Perdamai, berkerja sama dengan tim medis di klinik kesehatan. Dokter dari puskesmas (klinik desa) telah merekomendasikan pasien untuk berpartisipasi dalam program pengujian mata. Spesialis mata maka akan memprioritaskan operasi berdasarkan pada sejumlah faktor, misalnya beberapa pasien yang mungkin memiliki tekanan darah terlalu tinggi akan dioperasi. Pasien-pasien ini akan diberikan obat untuk mengurangi tekanan darah mereka dan menawarkan alternatif pilihan untuk menghilangkan katarak mereka. Hal ini dapat tercakupi kembali ketika acara komunitas Perdamai/Besi Pae bersama. Diharapkan lebih dari 100 operasi katarak akan dilakukan pada bulan Mei.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Kami sangat berterima kasih sekali lagi untuk semua dukungan Anda.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(18, 64, '2016-04-25', 'Update Operasi Katarak 1 Mei 2016', '<p>Untuk Semua,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kita telah terdaftar 350 orang untuk melakukan tes uji mata oleh Dokter Tim Perdami Eye pada hari Minggu 1 Mei minggu depan. Tim Perdami kemudian akan memilih 120 hingga 150 orang yang akan memiliki operasi katarak dari hari Senin hingga Rabu, pekan depan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Perdami telah mengirimkan semua peralatan mereka, yang mencakup mikroskop dan peralatan bedah lainnya, untuk Soe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ruangan operasi saat ini sedang dipersiapkan oleh relawan Besi Pae, untuk memastikan itu adalah lingkungan yang steril.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kami berterima kasih kepada Anda semua lagi atas dukungan Anda dan kami akan memberikan update tambahan minggu depan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Salam</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Besi Pae</p>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
